Web Coffee Chat

Technical details	
Submit file	./src/main/java/*.java, pom.xml or build.gradle, README.md, etc.
I want my Coffee on the Web!
Objective
Build a coffee shop application using Java Servlets, JSP (JavaServer Pages), and the MVC (Model-View-Controller) design pattern. The application will allow customers to place orders and view their order statuses through a web interface.

Application Overview
This coffee shop application will enable customers to:

View different types of coffee available for order.

Place orders and check their statuses.

Communicate with baristas via a simple chat interface (simulated via form submissions).

Requirements
1. Project Structure
Organize your project into the following directories:

coffee-shop-app/
|-- src/
|   |-- model/
|   |-- controller/
|   |-- service/
|-- web/
|   |-- WEB-INF/
|       |-- web.xml
|       |-- views/
|           |-- index.jsp
|           |-- orders.jsp
|-- lib/
2. Implementations
A. Model Layer
Define the data models for the application.
Example Coffee.java

package model;

public class Coffee {
    private String type;
    private double price;

    public Coffee(String type, double price) {
        this.type = type;
        this.price = price;
    }

    public String getType() {
        return type;
    }

    public double getPrice() {
        return price;
    }
}
