D. View Layer
Create JSP files to render the user interface.
Example index.jsp

<%@ page contentType="text/html;charset=UTF-8" language="java" %>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Coffee Shop</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Welcome to the Coffee Shop</h1>
<form action="coffeeshop" method="post">
    <label for="coffeeType">Choose your coffee:</label>
    <select name="coffeeType" id="coffeeType">
        <c:forEach var="coffee" items="${coffees}">
            <option value="${coffee.type}">${coffee.type} - {coffee.price}</option>
        </c:forEach>
    </select>
    <input type="submit" value="Order">
</form>
<a href="coffeeshop/orders">View Orders</a>
</body>
</html>
Example orders.jsp

<%@ page contentType="text/html;charset=UTF-8" language="java" %>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Orders</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Current Orders</h1>
<table>
    <tr>
        <th>Order ID</th>
        <th>Coffee Type</th>
        <th>Status</th>
    </tr>
    <c:forEach var="order" items="${orders}">
        <tr>
            <td>${order.id}</td>
            <td>${order.coffeeType}</td>
            <td>${order.status}</td>
        </tr>
    </c:forEach>
</table>
<a href="coffeeshop">Back to Coffee Shop</a>
</body>
</html>
3. Web Configuration
Configure the web application by defining the web.xml file.
Example web.xml

<web-app xmlns="http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee" 
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee 
         http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee/web-app_3_1.xsd"
         version="3.1">

    <servlet>
        <servlet-name>CoffeeShopController</servlet-name>
        [...]
    </servlet>

    <servlet-mapping>
        <servlet-name>CoffeeShopController</servlet-name>
        [...]
    </servlet-mapping>

    <servlet>
        <servlet-name>OrderController</servlet-name>
        [...]
    </servlet>

    <servlet-mapping>
        <servlet-name>OrderController</servlet-name>
        [...]
    </servlet-mapping>
</web-app>
4. Running the Application
Package the application as a WAR file.

Deploy it on a servlet container like Apache Tomcat.

Access the application via a web browser at http://localhost:8080/coffee-shop-app/coffeeshop.

